Done. Both outputs are written to the working directory:

- `transcript.json` (25 iterations, 28 hypotheses, 28 analyses, schema-valid)
- `analysis_summary.txt`

**Headline finding:** Three independently-randomized treatments (`feature_001`, `feature_014`, `feature_021`) act *synergistically* — only the all-three combination produces benefit (ORR 16-17% for any single or pairwise combination, jumping to 78.6% only when all three are co-administered). The synergy is fully abolished if either `feature_026=1` or `feature_009=1` (each independently sufficient to nullify it). Interestingly, those two modifiers have **zero** main effect on ORR in untreated patients — they are pure treatment-effect modifiers, not baseline prognostic markers.

**Final subgroup definition** (n=1,790 patients, 3.6% of cohort, ORR 78.60% vs 16.53% in everyone else; RD = +62.1 pp; OR ~ 18.6):

> `feature_001 = 1 AND feature_014 = 1 AND feature_021 = 1 AND feature_026 = 0 AND feature_009 = 0`

`feature_004` (3-level baseline prognostic gradient, likely cytogenetic/ELN risk) further grades response within this subgroup (86% / 77% / 67% across levels 0/1/2) but does not change whether the triple treatment works.
